 JOHANNESBURG - In the aftermath of the 1976 Soweto Uprising, one family was left with more questions than answers after Mbuyisa Makhubu vanished without a trace. Makhubu is the man carrying a dying Hector Pieterson in the iconic June 16 image. His relatives have been searching for him since the late 1970s. eNCA contributor Mpho Lakaje caught up with them. 